data.title: SUSHI: Semi-blind Unmixing with Sparsity for Hyperspectral Images
data.name: SUSHI

evidence: "This is the repository for the SUSHI (Semi-blind Unmixing with Sparsity for hyperspectral images) algorithm."

"The purpose of SUSHI is to perform non-stationary unmixing of hyperspectral images." and description of mapping physical parameters from hyperspectral data, indicating it directly performs scientific analysis.

Instructions focus on cloning/using notebooks and setting up a conda environment from the repo ("In this repositery, you will find: * *SUSHI Test Notebook.ipynb* ... * *SUSHI.py:* The SUSHI code itself"), with no mention of package managers or releases, implying distribution via the source repository.
